The paper focuses on the emotions experienced by developers during programming tasks, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves the use of biometric sensors to recognize emotions, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses strategies for dealing with negative emotions, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
